      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JUST A JOY (1) had the drop on the lead before drawing clear to score (17.60) at this track in Grade 4 over 300m. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. Well placed and will be tough to beat. MISS TWIX (6) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fourth (17.95) in a Grade 4 at this track. Solid record here at the distance winning four races. Should be about the money. GOLDEN SUNSET (2) flew the lids from out wide with a slick early split but ran over at the finish when a narrow fourth (17.67) over 300m at this track. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Likely to be about the mark. LET'S TROT WILL (4) was out of the money at this circuit last start but can turn the form around.",
